related_questions.question: What herb is cassia?
related_questions.snippet: Cassia cinnamon (Cinnamomum aromaticum) is made from the dried inner bark of an evergreen tree. It's the most common type of cinnamon sold in North America. Cassia cinnamon contains chemicals that seem to improve insulin sensitivity, which might help blood sugar control in people with diabetes.

related_questions.question: Is cassia as healthy as cinnamon?
related_questions.snippet: Cassia contains a lot of coumarin, which can be toxic in large quantities. It is much safer to choose Ceylon if you eat a lot of cinnamon.
